t19.text: The lady I sang next to has a stall with her husband at Salamanca Market. Yesterday was their last day of trading for the foreseeable future. The stall is their only income.

t20.text: There were enough of us (76 choristers, the orchestra and soloists) to give each other a rousing applause once the recording stopped. It was a strange but nice moment. We’re all in these uncertain times together.

t21.text: We did everything we would normally do for a concert but this time there was no audience. It was of course most notable at the end when we’d sung our hearts out and there was no applause.

t22.text: We were filmed (thank you @TasSymphony for organising this) and I’m looking forward to sharing the link with those who had planned to come to the concert, but also with friends who live too far away to see us perform.

t23.text: Last night I sang the Brahms Requiem for the second time with @TasSymphony. But it was the first time in my 12 years with the chorus we have performed to an empty hall. The concert was the finale of the Brahmsiana festivalpic.twitter.com/NFnI1D7mOn
